---
name: review-ticket
description: Review the PR attached to a {{backend.displayName}} ticket at a user-chosen depth, then check the diff delivers every acceptance criterion and project convention. PR-only — refuses if no PR exists. Use when the user asks to review a ticket or its PR — e.g. "review the PR", "is {{eg.prefixUpper}}-312 ready", "does this meet the acceptance criteria".
argument-hint: "{{eg.prefixUpper}}-NNN"
---

Review the PR attached to ticket {{arg}}. This skill works **only** on top of a PR — it never reviews a loose local diff.

{{> arg-guard}}

## 1. Resolve the PR

- {{op "getAttachedPR"}}. {{> preflight}}
- If no PR is found, ask the user for the PR number or URL.
- If none can be supplied — **hard stop**: "No PR found for {{arg}}. Run `/execute-ticket {{arg}}` first; review-ticket only works on top of a PR." Do not fall back to reviewing the working tree.

## 2. Ask for review depth — always

Even if a depth seems obvious, {{ask "review depth — low (shallow, high-confidence only), medium (standard), high (broader, may include uncertain findings), or max (deepest single pass); and whether findings go to chat only or also as inline PR comments"}}.

## 3. Gather ticket context

- {{> artifact-read}}
- Extract the acceptance criteria / user stories (the contracted scope) and any constraints flagged in the description.

## 4. Run the code review

{{codeReview}}

## 5. Scope check + verdict

After the review, add the ticket-scope layer the generic review doesn't know about:

- **Scope check:** does the PR diff actually deliver each acceptance criterion / user story from step 3? List any criterion not covered by the diff.
- **Convention check:** anything that violates the project conventions:
{{#each review.conventionChecks}}  - {{this}}.
{{/each}}{{#unless review.conventionChecks}}  - (none configured — skip).
{{/unless}}

End with a clear verdict, stated in chat AND recorded:

- `✅ Ready to merge` — no blocking findings, scope delivered; or
- `🟡 Needs changes` — list the blocking findings and uncovered criteria.

Record the **full review on the ticket** (not just in chat): {{op "addComment"}} with a structured review comment containing — the **verdict**; the **blocking** and **nice-to-have** findings grouped, each with a repo-root-relative `file:line`; any **uncovered acceptance criteria**; any **convention violations**; and the **PR link**. This comment is the durable record — inline PR comments (if you chose them in step 2) are *in addition*, not instead.

Then {{> artifact-write}} — fill the `Review verdict` section with the verdict **and the list of blocking findings / uncovered criteria**, so `/merge-ticket` can confirm they were addressed. `/merge-ticket` reads this verdict to decide whether review is done.

If the verdict is `🟡 Needs changes`, hand off: the findings are now on the PR, so suggest `/fix-ticket {{arg}}` to triage and address them (failing CI included), then re-review.

## Output shape

- Findings grouped: blocking vs nice-to-have. File references repo-root relative with line numbers.
- End with the PR URL and the ticket URL.
